    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nUsing neovim as a previewer for FZF is broken, the textfile is not displayed in the preview window - this is a regression.\r\n\r\nThis problem does not exist in NVIM v0.8.4 (commit b1ae775de618e3e87954a88d533ec17bbef41cdf) but does exist in master and NVIM v0.9.6 (commit 3a80c6ad18804ade71b9c59321592d391645bbd9):\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\necho \"foobar\" | fzf --preview \"nvim -R somefile.txt\"\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe text file should be displayed in the preview window\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nmaster\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nsort of\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFreeBSD 14\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nurxvt\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom source",
    "closed_at": null,
